    <apex:pageBlock title="Assigning Licenses">
        <p>When your trial period expires you will have to choose the users that are allowed to use Phonedeck. Go to the <a href="/0A3?setupid=ImportedPackage" target="_blank">Installed Packages</a> setup page to assign licenses.</p>
    </apex:pageBlock>
    <apex:pageBlock title="Required Permissions">
        <p>You have to grant permissions by assigning the <b>Phonedeck Standard User</b> permission set to the Phonedeck users. Salesforce has an excellent blog entry about <a href="http://blogs.salesforce.com/product/2011/12/permission-sets-best-practice-mass-assign-permission-sets-and-other-cool-things-using-the-api.html" target="_blank">assigning permission sets to multiple users</a>.</p>
    </apex:pageBlock>
	<apex:pageBlock title="Configure SoftPhone Layout">
        <p>The remote control functions of Phonedeck are integrated as a Salesforce OpenCTI 2.0 softphone. To configure how to react to incoming calls, configure a softphone layout at <a href="/04n" target="_blank">Setup > Customize > Call Center > SoftPhone Layouts</a>.</p>
    </apex:pageBlock>    
	<apex:pageBlock title="Assign Call Center">
        <p>Phonedeck users can control their phones using Salesforce's Softphone widget. The widget can be enabled by assigning the Phonedeck call center to the users. To assign a call center, please follow the <a href="https://help.salesforce.com/apex/HTViewHelpDoc?id=cti_admin_manageagentsadd.htm&language=en" target="_blank">official documentation</a>.</p>
    </apex:pageBlock>
</apex:page>